<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED
        BEARINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1300704" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED BEARINGS</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The shimming procedure can be done in the horizontal or vertical position. The procedure is done
                    the same.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Shims must be aligned properly or else the rear bearing cover may be damaged when final torque is
                    applied.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft straps. Make sure a 0.100 countershaft rear bearing shim is
                installed (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q0">Figure 260</hotlnk>). Be sure the countershaft rear bearing races are seated
                in the bearing bores.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q0" filename="../figg13/G13007Q0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 260. Install Countershaft Rear Bearing Shim</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) clean 3/8" x 1" bolts without washers directly across from each other in
                each bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q1">Figure 261</hotlnk>). Tapped holes in auxiliary case must be free of thread
                adhesive.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q1" filename="../figg13/G13007Q1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 261. Install Bolts in Bearing Covers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to 7 in-lbs. (0.8 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q2">Figure 262</hotlnk>).
                <emph type="bold">Do not install the countershaft rear bearing cover gasket.</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q2" filename="../figg13/G13007Q2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 262. Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the output shaft six (6) times clockwise, then six (6) times counterclockwise to seat
                the countershaft rear bearings. Use a feeler gauge, as close to each bolt location as possible, and
                measure the gap between the countershaft rear bearing cover and the auxiliary case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q3">Figure 263</hotlnk>). Record the measurements. Using the average measurement,
                refer to the
                <hotlnk xrefid="t1300701">Shimming Chart</hotlnk>
                to identify proper shim.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q3" filename="../figg13/G13007Q3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 263. Measure Gap Between Countershaft Rear Bearing Cover and Auxiliary Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing cover and gauging shim.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the selected shim on the rear countershaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q4">Figure 264</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q4" filename="../figg13/G13007Q4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 264. Place Shim on Rear Countershaft Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on countershaft rear bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q4">Figure 264</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the countershaft rear bearing cover over the new gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007q5">Figure 265</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007q5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007q5" filename="../figg13/G13007Q5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 265. Tighten Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat Steps 1-8 for the other countershaft rear bearing cover.</para>
        </step1>
